e750a82c-9578-4281-a228-f32ec81c9571	ff68e952-b7ee-4034-af62-07c9d79660f1	Law 1: Make It Obvious (Cue)	\N	<p>To begin a new habit, the cue must be clear. Habit Stacking is a technique that links a new desired habit to an existing one. The formula is: "After \\[Current Habit\\], I will \\[New Habit\\]". For example, "After I pour my morning coffee, I will meditate for one minute." This leverages the automaticity of the existing habit to trigger the new one. Environment Design notes that the environment is the invisible hand that shapes behavior. Make cues for good habits a prominent part of the environment. To encourage reading, place a book on the pillow. To drink more water, place a water bottle in multiple visible locations throughout the day.</p>	https://media.lilde.com/media/%40_The-Stable-Reset/MP3/021.mp3	\N	\N	21	OVERFLOW	0	0	2025-10-17 16:40:10.024858	2025-11-07 16:45:49.087572	light	0.00	0.00	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
dce2212f-0610-46db-8080-c7f2a842c014	ff68e952-b7ee-4034-af62-07c9d79660f1	Law 4: Make It Satisfying (Reward)	\N	<p>The human brain evolved to prioritize immediate rewards over delayed ones. Good habits often have a delayed return, while bad habits have an immediate one. The cardinal rule of behavior change is: what is immediately rewarded is repeated. Find a way to give oneself an immediate reward, an immediate sense of success after completing a good habit. This could be as simple as putting a checkmark on a calendar or transferring money into a savings account after skipping an unnecessary purchase. Habit Tracking is a form of immediate gratification. A habit trackera calendar, a journal, or an appprovides visual proof of progress and creates a satisfying feeling of accomplishment, which encourages repetition. It also reinforces the principle of "never miss twice." Missing once is an accident; missing twice is the start of a new, undesirable habit.</p>	https://media.lilde.com/media/%40_The-Stable-Reset/MP3/024.mp3	\N	\N	24	OVERFLOW	0	0	2025-10-17 16:40:10.024858	2025-11-07 16:46:03.254065	light	0.00	0.00	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
